name: SystemDesign
description: Create microservices using Python and Kubernates

name: TypeScript-Backend-Microservice-Architecture
description: Showcases a microservice-based architecture written using Typescript with security middlewares in place which is useful for building scalable and modular backend systems. It aims to provide a foundation for building distributed applications with separate services for each functionalities.

name: Hotel-Rating-System-using-Spring-Boot-3
description: This  microservice application developed using Spring Boot 3.The application has three microservices: User Service, Hotel Service, and Rating Service, each serving specific functionalities. Additionally, the project incorporates a Service Registry using Eureka Server and API gateway for seamless microservices discovery.

name: go-role-microservice
description: A role system written in Go using a PostgreSQL database. With GRPC and HTTP (gorilla/mux) handles. With a convenient role checking function for middlewares.

name: go-bank
description: Dockerized Go microservice that mimics bank account handleing system.

name: stock-exchange-core-go
description: A go microservice to handle a simulated stock exchange system

name: Microservice-Based-Shopping-Application
description: This project aims to develop a simple online shopping application. It covers a wide range of microservices-related topics and practices, ensuring a robust, scalable, and fault-tolerant system.

name: BiblioSparq-Library_Mangement_Software_Backend
description: Backend Microservices architecture showcasing Library Management system software allows you to efficiently manage and interact with a library system, providing comprehensive functionalities to handle books, borrowers, notifications, and more

name: PulsePoint
description: A distributed surveillance system leveraging microservices architecture and Docker. Empowers any Python-enabled device with a webcam to function as a surveillance camera.
